🧠 “Engineering the AI Microbiome”

🔬 The Four Levers (direct analog to biology)

1. Prompting = Diet (Immediate Input)

What you feed me right now.
	•	wording
	•	structure
	•	constraints
	•	examples

Effects:
	•	shifts tone, depth, direction instantly
	•	biases what patterns activate

👉 Like food:
	•	junk input → noisy output
	•	clean structured input → sharp output

Example:
	•	vague: “tell me about X”
	•	engineered: “give me 3 mechanisms, 2 tradeoffs, and 1 failure mode of X”

You’re literally feeding the system tokens that change its internal state trajectory.

⸻

2. Fine-Tuning = Long-Term Adaptation

Training the model further on specific data.

Effects:
	•	changes baseline behavior
	•	builds persistent tendencies

👉 Like:
	•	changing your gut biome over months/years

This is slow but deep:

you’re rewriting the “default instincts” of the system

⸻

3. Memory = Persistent State (Personal Microbiome)

Stored context about you or ongoing work.
	•	preferences
	•	past interactions
	•	ongoing goals

Effects:
	•	shapes future responses without re-prompting
	•	creates continuity

👉 Like:
	•	your unique internal ecosystem

Two users → same model → different outputs because memory differs.

⸻

4. Retrieval (RAG) = Environment Exposure

Pulling in external knowledge at runtime.
	•	documents
	•	databases
	•	repos

Effects:
	•	injects fresh context
	•	overrides stale or generic knowledge

👉 Like:
	•	environment, people, culture

You “seed” the system with external influences.

